Add support for single sign-on to Android SDKSummary: This change adds support for single sign-on to the Android SDK as announced here: http://developers.facebook.com/blog/post/423nnThis change is mostly transparent and should require only a few updates to your code. You'll need to modify your code as follows:nn* Move your applicationId from the authorize method to the constructor for the Facebook classn* Insert a call to the authorizeCallback() method at the top of your Activity's onActivityResult() function.n* Register your Android key hash in the Facebook developer application.nnNote that stream dialogs do not yet work with single sign on, but we will add support soon.nnFor more details, check the README file. If you have issues or bugs, please report them to: https://github.com/facebook/facebook-android-sdk/issuesnn[ Note: this is a squashed commit with contributions from Yariv Sadan, Jim Brusstar, Arun Vijayvergiya, Brent Goldman, and Luke Shepard]n

[android-sdk] Adds basic single-request logic to Request/Response classes.Summary:nThis commit changes our HTTP stack from the Apache HttpClient stack to the HttpURLConnection stack, whichnthe Android development team has suggested is the stack to use going forward. Basic functionality for single (i.e.,nnon-batched) requests is functional, with many caveats. There is no (de-)serialization of GraphObjects as of yet, so mostnrequests to Graph API will not result in a Response that is useful for anything (though the debugger can be used tonverify that JSONObjects in the right shape are being created). There is no support for requests that return JSONArraysnrather than JSONObjects. There are a million TODO port: comments indicating where functional parity with iOS is stillnlacking.nnTest Plan:n- Ran unit testsnnRevert Plan:nnReviewers: mmarucheck, jacl, gregschechte, aydennnReviewed By: mmaruchecknnCC: msdkexp@nnDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.fb.com/D501547n

[android-sdk] Added support for collections in GraphObject wrapper.Summary:nAdded basic support for properties that get/set collections on a GraphObject.nCollections of primitive types and GraphObjects are supported. A GraphObjectCollectionnclass provides additional functionality beyond a Collection, including casting thenentire collection to a GraphObjectCollection of another GraphObject type. (Castingncollections of non-GraphObjects is not supported, as we don't proxy non-GraphObjects.)nnTODOs remain around fully supporting putting collections, as we need to ensure thatnwe are storing the underlying JSONArray, if applicable.nnTest Plan:n- Ran unit testsnnRevert Plan:nnReviewers: jacl, mmarucheck, gregschechte, aydennnReviewed By: mmaruchecknnCC: msdkexp@, platform-diffs@listsnnDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.fb.com/D510578n

Implemented file-based cache for Android SDKSummary:nThis implements a thread-safe cache for the Android SDK.  Itnsupports the following features:n- Read/write/clearn- Writes are supported both directly (create an OutputStreamn  and write to it) and indirectly (clone an InputStream fromn  some other source).n- Quotas based on file count and total byte count.n- Quota enforced in LRU order where both reads and writesn  update the timestamp.n- Multiple instances with separate quotas.n- The implementation is thread-safe--all public methods can ben  safely called from multiple threads without synchronization.n- Only File-based operations are needed--there is no sqliten  dependency.nnTest Plan:nnew unit testsnnRevert Plan: OKnnReviewers: clang, jaclnnReviewed By: clangnnCC: msdkexp@nnDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.fb.com/D512569nnTask ID: 1168131n

[android-sdk] Added TestSession, FacebookTestCase, TestBlocker.Summary:nThis commit adds a TestSession class, which serves much the same purpose as the FBTestSession class innthe iOS SDK. It allows test accounts to be created in either a shared or private mode. In shared mode,nthe permissions of the test account are encoded as part of its name, so future test cases can re-usenthe same test account rather than create a new one. In private mode, a test account is created with thennecessary permissions and then deleted at the end of the session, to avoid proliferation of test accounts.n(The encoding of permissions is done using the String.hash method, which will be different than the encodingnused on iOS, so test accounts will not be shared between the two platforms at the moment, and there is a verynsmall possibility of hash code collisions that could result in permissions-related errors. The possibility isnpretty remote.)nnAdded a FacebookTestCase that simplifies use of TestSession by reading in applicationId and applicationSecretnfrom a config.json file that is created by the new configure_unit_tests.sh script, similar to what we didnfor iOS.nnTestBlocker provides message-pumping-and-waiting functionality similar to FBTestBlocker. Given the synchronousnnature of calls on Android, TestBlocker will not be needed as frequently as on iOS, but it is needed to testnsession authorization, which happens asynchronously, as well as obviously any asynchronous-specific test cases.nnMade necessary changes to some classes (AccessToken, Session) to make certain members have default visibilitynrather than private, in order to let TestSession override functionality it needed to. Session can now take anhandler passed in from outside rather than using its own, which is necessary to correctly pump messages throughnthe TestBlocker's handler in test cases.nnFixed up some code in Response that was incorrectly handling Facebook returning naked 'true' or 'false' responses.nnTest Plan:n- Ran all unit testsnnRevert Plan:nnReviewers: mmarucheck, jacl, ayden, gregschechtennReviewed By: mmaruchecknnCC: msdkexp@, security-diffs@listsnnDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.fb.com/D514919n

[ios-sdk] Added Logger class, fixed bugs in Request, unit test cleanupSummary:nAdded a Logger class, analogous to FBLogger in the iOS SDK. The logger uses the underlying Log infrastructurenfor logging, but checks the logging behavior flags in Settings to determine what to log. It also supportsnreplacement of access tokens in generated logs.nnAdded request/response logging.nnRequest was not setting access tokens correctly for non-batched requests.nnAnnotated all unit tests with @Small/Medium/LargeTest to help developers create debug configurations for differentnpurposes (e.g., run Small/Medium as part of a TDD flow and Large only as integration/checkin tests).nnRefined TestBlocker to remove the need to call reset() between uses.nnAdded machineUniqueUserTag to TestSession for parity with iOS SDK.nnTest Plan:n- Ran unit testsnnRevert Plan:nnReviewers: jacl, mmarucheck, gregschechte, aydennnReviewed By: jaclnnCC: msdkexp@, platform-diffs@listsnnDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.fb.com/D518850n

Enable caching last-token-updated timestampSummary:nThere was only a single method for setting the access token on thenFacebook class (setAccessToken()).  This did not distinguish betweennsetting a token loaded from cache vs.  setting a new token resultingnfrom authorization.nnSince setAccessToken() updates the last-token-updated timestamp, andnsince this timestamp is used to determine when to refresh the token,nit always looked like the token had just been updated when the app'snActivity started.  This meant the Facebook class would never try tonrefresh the token.nnTo fix this, the Facebook class now supports getting the value of thenlast-token-updated timestamp, and also supports restoring this alongnwith the token value and expiration timestamp in a single operation.nnThis also updates Hackbook to demonstrate caching.nnTest Plan:n- ant build Hackbookn- Ran Hackbook, verified that we could get and restore the timestamp.nnRevert Plan:nsafe to revertnnTags:nnReviewers: clang, vijaye, caabernathynnReviewed By: clangnnCC: msdkexp@nnDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.fb.com/D552473nnTask ID: 1363221n

Add support for request cachingSummary:nWe now support caching the results from a batch of requests.nnThis adds a public RequestBatch class that implements List<Request>,nbut also provides a scope for adding more metadata about the request.nThis includes the Handler previously passed as a separate parameter,nas well as the new caching parameters.nnRequestBatch.cacheKey controls the key used to load from and to savento for cache results of a request.nnRequestBatch.forceRoundTrip controls whether we do a roundtrip withoutnattempting to load from cache.  If cacheKey is set and forceRoundTripnis true, we will fetch new results and update the cache.nnA future change will reduce the number of overloads by requiringnRequestBatch for scenarios that involve batching or parameters relatednto RequestBatch.nnTest Plan:nUnit testsnnRevert Plan:nok to revertnnTags:nnReviewers: clang, mingfli, karthiksnnReviewed By: clangnnCC: msdkexp@nnDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.fb.com/D554389nnTask ID: 1406500n

[android-sdk] Enable StrictMode in unit tests; do not try to hit network or disk from UI thread in SDK classes.Summary:nGingerbread introduced a new StrictMode which allows setting per-thread policies that can take various actions, upnto killing the process, if certain operations are performed on the thread. Honeycomb made the defaults stricter.nWe should avoid performing any I/O operations on the UI thread, to ensure that apps using StrictMode do not encounternany unexpected exceptions.nnRequestAsyncTask will now perform request serialization on the background thread, rather than the calling thread. Thisnmeans any serialization errors will now have to be handled in the request callback rather than at the time the tasknis created.nnFriend/Place picker image downloading will now only hit the cache from a worker thread, not from the UI thread.nnUnit tests will now turn StrictMode on for the UI thread, but leave it off for all other threads. A helper existsnto turn it on for any given thread if desired.nnTest Plan:n- Ran unit testsn- Ran FriendPickerSamplen- Ran PlacePickerSamplen- Ran Scrumptiousn- Ran BooleanOGnnRevert Plan:nnReviewers: mmarucheck, mingfli, karthiksnnReviewed By: mmaruchecknnCC: ekoneil, platform-diffs@listsnnDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.fb.com/D589323nnTask ID: 1776253n

[android-sdk] Make HelloFacebook more robust when handling pending actions.Summary:nPreviously, a race condition existed in HelloFacebook where handlePendingActions could be called before all conditionsnnecessary to successfully call the pending action were in place. In particular, a cancelled permissions upgrade wouldncause us to attempt to post a photo or status update anyway. Added a handler so that cancelling the permissions upgradenwill display an informative message and abort the attempt to post. Improved the pending action handlers so they will notnattempt an action if all necessary conditions are not met, but will instead stay in the pending state until they arencalled again. (For instance, we may be called because this.user was filled in, while we are still waiting for a pendingnpermissions upgrade -- now, we'll recognize that we aren't ready to execute the pending action and will wait for thenpermissions upgrade to complete.)nnTest Plan:n- Ran HelloFacebook on device with Facebook app installed and Don't keep activities developer option onn- Logged on as user who had not TOSed appn- Clicked Post Photon- Hit back button rather than agreeing to permissions upgraden- Saw warning messagen- Clicked Post Photo againn- Accepted permissions upgraden- Saw that photo was posted upon returning to appnnRevert Plan:nnReviewers: mmarucheck, mingfli, karthiks, gregschechtennReviewed By: mingflinnDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.fb.com/D614469nnTask ID: 1846373n

Fix memory leak in LoginManager and AppEventsLoggerLoginManager's context and loginLogger both hold a reference to thenactivity starting the login. This activity is leaked if the login processnis canceled. It is also leaked if finishLogin() is never called, e.g. whennthe device's configuration/orientation is changed. finishLogin() only nullsnout context and loginLogger in case of a successful login.nnThis commit updates LoginManager and AppEventsLogger, so that it is notnrequired anymore to hold a reference to the activity starting the login.n

Silently catch exceptions from invalid enum values (#544)Summary:nYour current SDK crashes all the time for real users:n```njava.lang.IllegalArgumentException:n   at java.lang.Enum.valueOf (Enum.java:257)n   at com.facebook.appevents.codeless.internal.EventBinding$MappingMethod.valueOf (EventBinding.java:154)n at com.facebook.appevents.codeless.internal.EventBinding.getInstanceFromJson (EventBinding.java:82)n  at com.facebook.appevents.codeless.internal.EventBinding.parseArray (EventBinding.java:69)n  at com.facebook.appevents.codeless.CodelessMatcher$ViewMatcher.run (CodelessMatcher.java:224)n  at android.os.Handler.handleCallback (Handler.java:789)n  at android.os.Handler.dispatchMessage (Handler.java:98)n  at android.os.Looper.loop (Looper.java:164)n  at android.app.ActivityThread.main (ActivityThread.java:6944)n  at java.lang.reflect.Method.invoke (Native Method)n  at com.android.internal.os.Zygote$MethodAndArgsCaller.run (Zygote.java:327)n  at com.android.internal.os.ZygoteInit.main (ZygoteInit.java:1374)n```nnThere already is a bug report for this but it has not been worked on yet because it is stuck in need more info state:nhttps://developers.facebook.com/support/bugs/278547559523105/nnLooks like this comes from invalid/unexpected values delivered by your codeless configuration JSON data.nnWhat this change doesn--nThis change fixes the uncaught exceptions by catching them to avoid the resulting crashes. Imho this should be done anyway for incoming data processing and should have been done from the start of this feature.nnWhat this change doesn't don--nThe unexpected values in the configuration data have to be handled somehow of course but this is out of the scope of this fix.nnMiscn--nTo whom it may concern: your pull request template seems to be out of date. It tells me to issue my pull request against your `:dev` branch but there is no such branch.nPull Request resolved: https://github.com/facebook/facebook-android-sdk/pull/544nnReviewed By: wi3launnDifferential Revision: D13948378nnPulled By: jingping2015nnfbshipit-source-id: 2bbe6fd40dad62360f0eec3f27e00d46b284c580n
